(14, 1, '2015-07-12 17:15:17', '2015-07-12 17:15:17', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/images/panasonic_eluga_z_champagne_gold.jpg" alt="" width="635" height="475" />\r\n<div class="preview-body-holder removable-parent order-handle">\r\n<div id="vbid-adc2d-sltrbzqgwe" class="preview-element preview-body magic-circle-holder text-element quick-text-style-menu" data-menu-name="PREVIEW_BODY">\r\n\r\nPanasonic recently launched a new smartphone in India, the Eluga Z. It has been priced at Rs. 13,490. The smartphone is expected to be available in the market by second week of July in Champagne Gold, Ivory White, and Midnight Blue color variants.It also ships with a flip cover, protective case and screen guard. Its specifications are as follows:-\r\n\r\n*Dual SIM\r\n\r\n*Android 4.4.2 Kitkat\r\n\r\n*5-inch (720x1280 pixel) Amoled display\r\n\r\n*1.4GHz Octa-core processor\r\n\r\n*2GB RAM\r\n\r\n*13-megapixel rear camera with LED flash, and a 5-megapixel front facing camera\r\n\r\n*2050mAh battery (Fast charging support)\r\n\r\n*Dimensions- 141.3x70.6x6.85mm and weighs 120 grams\r\n\r\n*3G\r\n\r\n*USB OTG\r\n\r\n*Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n with hotspot and direct functionality\r\n\r\n*GPS/ A-GPS\r\n\r\n*Bluetooth 4.0 with EDR\r\n\r\n*Ambient light sensor, proximity sensor, e-compass, and accelerometer\r\n\r\nSpeaking on the launch, Manish Sharma (Managing Director, Panasonic India) said, "With an aim to meet the needs of our consumers and their changing needs, the new smartphone showcases the convergence of Panasonic''s pioneering technology and consumer insight. The device offers great functionality and design, accompanied by a comprehensive system of applications that reliably address the needs of our evolving customers."\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n(Image source- http://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/images/panasonic_eluga_z_champagne_gold.jpg)', 'Panasonic Eluga Z', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'panasonic-eluga-z', '', '', '2015-07-12 18:23:23', '2015-07-12 18:23:23', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=14', 0, 'post', '', 0),
