(23, 1, '2015-07-12 17:22:31', '2015-07-12 17:22:31', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Apple-Music.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720" />\r\n\r\nApple finally released its online music streaming application "Apple Music" on 30th of June . Though it came in the market very late, but like its said "Better late than never". Users now have an option to stream their favorite music right from the application or they can buy the music individually from the iTunes Store. Their previously purchased music and the playlist will be automatically synced with the application after the update. The music runs on a slightly lower 250 kbps bitrate, but it is encoded using AAC. Along with the application, Apple also released its radio station Beats 1. Now, lets see if the giant gives any tough competition to the much renowned  applications such as Spotify, Soundcloud, Saavn etc. Which are already ruling the market.\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Apple-Music.jpg)', 'Apple Music', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'apple-music', '', '', '2015-07-12 18:23:09', '2015-07-12 18:23:09', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=23', 0, 'post', '', 0),
