(29, 1, '2015-07-12 17:26:26', '2015-07-12 17:26:26', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://static1.gamespot.com/uploads/original/1539/15391776/2901164-0977294496-windo.jpg" alt="" width="780" height="439" />\r\n\r\nMicrosoft is set to release its upcoming Windows 10 on the 29th of July 2015. It is finalizing its RTM build which is likely to be available by the end of this week. The Insider Preview (v10.0.10162) was released on 2nd July ie exactly 7 days ago. The RTM process has always been a significant milestone for the previous versions of the Windows, but this time it is more of a minor goal. With Microsoft moving the Windows 10 to a "Windows as a service" model which means that the product will be regularly updated. Moreover, that''s the reason why Windows 10 is considered as the final version of Windows as regular updates means its never really finished. Windows chief Terry Myerson also said "We will never be done" last week.\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://static1.gamespot.com/uploads/original/1539/15391776/2901164-0977294496-windo.jpg)', 'Windows 10 "RTM"', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'windows-10-rtm', '', '', '2015-07-12 18:22:50', '2015-07-12 18:22:50', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=29', 0, 'post', '', 0),
