(227, 1, '2015-08-14 10:45:48', '2015-08-14 05:15:48', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://gsminsider.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Lenovo-ZUK-Z1-close-up-image-GSMinsider-photo-2.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="488" />\r\n\r\nLenovo recently launched its new smartphone "Zuk Z1" in China. It has been priced at CNY 1,799 (Rs. 18,250) and supports a fingerprint scanner and USB Type-C port. It has been launched under Lenovo''s online only sub brand Zuk. It has a full metal frame. It will be available in White and Grey color variants and is expected to go on sale from 18th August. Its specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 5.1.1 Lollipop\r\n\r\n*5.5-Inch full-HD (1080x1920 pixels) display\r\n\r\n*2.5GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon 801 processor\r\n\r\n*Adreno 330 GPU\r\n\r\n*3GB RAM\r\n\r\n*64GB In-built storage\r\n\r\n*13MP Rear camera (Sony sensor (IMX214) and optical image stabilization) and a 8MP front camera\r\n\r\n*4100mAh Battery\r\n\r\n*FDD-LTE Band 3 1800MHz, TDD-LTE Band 40 2300MHz, Bluetooth 4.1, Wi-Fi a/b/g/n/ac, GPS and Glonass\r\n\r\n* Accelerometer, ambient light sensor, gyroscope, digital compass and proximity sensor\r\n\r\n*Dimensions: 155.7x77.3x8.9mm and weighs 175g\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://cdn.gsmarena.com/vv/newsimg/15/06/zuk-smartphone/gsmarena_001.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://gsminsider.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Lenovo-ZUK-Z1-close-up-image-GSMinsider-photo-2.jpg)\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.gsmarena.com/vv/newsimg/15/06/zuk-smartphone/gsmarena_001.jpg" alt="" width="580" height="326" />', 'Lenovo''s Zuk Z1', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '226-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-14 10:45:48', '2015-08-14 05:15:48', '', 226, 'http://thetechlog.in/2015/08/14/226-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(229, 1, '2015-08-16 19:30:26', '2015-08-16 14:00:26', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.gsmarena.com/imgroot/news/15/08/note5-benchmarks/-728xw2/main.jpg" alt="" width="728" height="410" />\r\n\r\nSamsung on Thursday launched its two new smartphones "Samsung Galaxy Note 5 and Galaxy S6 Edge+" in Galaxy Unpacked 2015 event in New York. Galaxy Note 5 has been priced at $739.99 (Rs.<span class="uccResult">48,400) </span>for the 32GB variant and $839.99 (Rs.<span class="uccResult">54,800) </span> for the 64GB variant. And Galaxy S6 Edge+ has been priced at $814.99 (Rs.<span class="uccResult">53,300) for the 32GB variant </span>and $914.99 (Rs.<span class="uccResult">59,800) </span>for the64GB variant. Both the devices have identical specifications expect for the fact that the Galaxy Note 5 will support a S Pen Stylus and a single curved edge. Both the devices will be available in White Pearl, Black Sapphire, Gold Platinum and Silver Titanium color variants. Their specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 5.1 Lollipop\r\n\r\n*64-Bit octa-core Exynos 7420 processor (Four Cortex-A57 cores clocked at 2.1GHz and four Cortex-A53 cores clocked at 1.5GHz)\r\n\r\n*5.7-Inch QHD (1440x2560 pixels) Super-Amoled display (515ppi)\r\n\r\n*4GB LPDDR4 RAM\r\n\r\n*16MP Rear camera and a 5MP front camera\r\n\r\n*Bluetooth 4.2, Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, GPS/ A-GPS, Micro-USB 2.0, 4G LTE, NFC and MST\r\n\r\n*Fingerprint scanner\r\n\r\n*3000mAh Battery\r\n\r\n*Samsung Galaxy Edge+ - Dimensions: 154.4x75.8x6.9mm and weighs 153g\r\n\r\n*Samsung Galaxy Note 5 - Dimensions: 153.2x76.1x7.6mm and weight of 171g\r\n\r\nAccording to JK Shin, "At Samsung, we believed in the promise that large screen smartphones could actively address some major consumers pain points by providing users with a better viewing experience and more productivity on-the-go. With the launch of the Galaxy S6 Edge+ and Note 5, we''re re-emphasizing our ongoing commitment to bold, fearless innovation that meets the needs of our consumers."\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://cdn.gsmarena.com/imgroot/news/15/08/note5-benchmarks/-728xw2/main.jpg)', 'Samsung Galaxy Note 5, Galaxy S6 Edge+ launched', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'samsung-galaxy-note-5-galaxy-s6-edge-launched', '', '', '2015-08-16 19:30:26', '2015-08-16 14:00:26', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=229', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(230, 1, '2015-08-16 19:29:54', '2015-08-16 13:59:54', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.gsmarena.com/imgroot/news/15/08/note5-benchmarks/-728xw2/main.jpg" alt="" width="728" height="410" />\r\n\r\nSamsung on Thursday launched its two new smartphones "Samsung Galaxy Note 5 and Galaxy S6 Edge+" in Galaxy Unpacked 2015 event in New York. Galaxy Note 5 has been priced at $739.99 (Rs.<span class="uccResult">48,400) </span>for the 32GB variant and $839.99 (Rs.<span class="uccResult">54,800) </span> for the 64GB variant. And Galaxy S6 Edge+ has been priced at $814.99 (Rs.<span class="uccResult">53,300) for the 32GB variant </span>and $914.99 (Rs.<span class="uccResult">59,800) </span>for the64GB variant. Both the devices have identical specifications expect for the fact that the Galaxy Note 5 will support a S Pen Stylus and a single curved edge. Both the devices will be available in White Pearl, Black Sapphire, Gold Platinum and Silver Titanium color variants. Their specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 5.1 Lollipop\r\n\r\n*64-Bit octa-core Exynos 7420 processor (Four Cortex-A57 cores clocked at 2.1GHz and four Cortex-A53 cores clocked at 1.5GHz)\r\n\r\n*5.7-Inch QHD (1440x2560 pixels) Super-Amoled display (515ppi)\r\n\r\n*4GB LPDDR4 RAM\r\n\r\n*16MP Rear camera and a 5MP front camera\r\n\r\n*Bluetooth 4.2, Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, GPS/ A-GPS, Micro-USB 2.0, 4G LTE, NFC and MST\r\n\r\n*Fingerprint scanner\r\n\r\n*3000mAh Battery\r\n\r\n*Samsung Galaxy Edge+ - Dimensions: 154.4x75.8x6.9mm and weighs 153g\r\n\r\n*Samsung Galaxy Note 5 - Dimensions: 153.2x76.1x7.6mm and weight of 171g\r\n\r\nAccording to JK Shin, "At Samsung, we believed in the promise that large screen smartphones could actively address some major consumers pain points by providing users with a better viewing experience and more productivity on-the-go. With the launch of the Galaxy S6 Edge+ and Note 5, we''re re-emphasizing our ongoing commitment to bold, fearless innovation that meets the needs of our consumers."\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://cdn.gsmarena.com/imgroot/news/15/08/note5-benchmarks/-728xw2/main.jpg)', 'Samsung Galaxy Note 5, Galaxy S6 Edge+ launched', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '229-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-16 19:29:54', '2015-08-16 13:59:54', '', 229, 'http://thetechlog.in/2015/08/16/229-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(249, 1, '2015-08-30 21:51:24', '2015-08-30 16:21:24', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.smartphoneandprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/micromax-canvas-nitro-2-e311-full-specifications.jpg" alt="" width="570" height="300" />\r\n\r\nMicromax recently launched its new smartphone "Canvas Nitro 4G" in India. It has been priced at Rs. 10,999 and supports LTE bands. Its specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 5.0.2 Lollipop\r\n\r\n*5-Inch HD (720x1280) IPS display (Corning Gorilla Glass 3)\r\n\r\n*1.5Ghz Snapdragon 415 octa-core processor\r\n\r\n*2GB LPDDR3 RAM\r\n\r\n*16GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 32GB)\r\n\r\n*13MP Rear camera (Dual LED) and a 5MP front camera\r\n\r\n*Bluetooth 4.0, Wi-Fi, Micro-USB and 4G\r\n\r\n*2500mAh Battery\r\n\r\nAccording to Vineet Taneja (CEO, Micromax Informatics) , "India is at the tipping point of 4G revolution and we expect the consumers to skip 3G and directly leap forward to 4G LTE connectivity. With the launch of Canvas Nitro 4G, we aim to bring a perfect combination of technology, rich features and a faster 4G experience at a great value to more and more consumers."\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://www.smartphoneandprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/micromax-canvas-nitro-2-e311-full-specifications.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://www.knowreviewtip.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/micromax-canvas-nitro-a311.jpeg)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.knowreviewtip.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/micromax-canvas-nitro-a311.jpeg" alt="" width="400" height="261" />', 'Micromax Canvas Nitro 4G', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'micromax-canvas-nitro-4g', '', '', '2015-08-30 21:52:02', '2015-08-30 16:22:02', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=249', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(232, 1, '2015-08-20 11:44:14', '2015-08-20 06:14:14', '<p><img class="alignnone" src="http://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Lenovo-A20102.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="828" /></p>\r\n<p>Lenovo recently launched its new smartphone "A2010" in India. It has been priced at Rs. 4,990 and will be exclusively available on Flipkart. It is a dual SIM device and supports 4G (FDD 1800MHz (Band 3) and TDD 2300MHz (Band 40)). Flash sale registrations will start on 3rd September at 3PM. It specifications are as following:-</p>\r\n<p>*Android 5.1 Lollipop</p>\r\n<p>*4.5-Inch FWVGA (480x854) display</p>\r\n<p>*1GHz MediaTek MT6735m 64-bit quad core processor</p>\r\n<p>*1GB RAM</p>\r\n<p>*8GB Inbuilt storage (Expandable upto 32GB)</p>\r\n<p>*5MP Rear camera and 2MP front camera</p>\r\n<p>*Bluetooth 4.0 LE, Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n and FM radio</p>\r\n<p>*2000mAh Battery</p>\r\n<p>*Dimensions: 130.5x66.6x9.98 mm</p>\r\n<p>According to Sudhin Mathur (Director,Smartphones, Lenovo India),"An Indian consumer is evolved and willing to move with the world. We at Lenovo are looking to bridge the gap between the latest technology and an Indian consumer by offering innovative and future-proof devices easily available to the masses at an affordable price. Lenovo A2010 is a step in this direction."</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Lenovo A2010 launched', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lenovo-a2010-launched', '', '', '2015-08-20 11:44:14', '2015-08-20 06:14:14', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=232', 0, 'post', '', 0),
