(226, 1, '2015-08-14 10:46:09', '2015-08-14 05:16:09', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://gsminsider.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Lenovo-ZUK-Z1-close-up-image-GSMinsider-photo-2.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="488" />\r\n\r\nLenovo recently launched its new smartphone "Zuk Z1" in China. It has been priced at CNY 1,799 (Rs. 18,250) and supports a fingerprint scanner and USB Type-C port. It has been launched under Lenovo''s online only sub brand Zuk. It has a full metal frame. It will be available in White and Grey color variants and is expected to go on sale from 18th August. Its specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 5.1.1 Lollipop\r\n\r\n*5.5-Inch full-HD (1080x1920 pixels) display\r\n\r\n*2.5GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon 801 processor\r\n\r\n*Adreno 330 GPU\r\n\r\n*3GB RAM\r\n\r\n*64GB In-built storage\r\n\r\n*13MP Rear camera (Sony sensor (IMX214) and optical image stabilization) and a 8MP front camera\r\n\r\n*4100mAh Battery\r\n\r\n*FDD-LTE Band 3 1800MHz, TDD-LTE Band 40 2300MHz, Bluetooth 4.1, Wi-Fi a/b/g/n/ac, GPS and Glonass\r\n\r\n* Accelerometer, ambient light sensor, gyroscope, digital compass and proximity sensor\r\n\r\n*Dimensions: 155.7x77.3x8.9mm and weighs 175g\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://cdn.gsmarena.com/vv/newsimg/15/06/zuk-smartphone/gsmarena_001.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://gsminsider.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Lenovo-ZUK-Z1-close-up-image-GSMinsider-photo-2.jpg)\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.gsmarena.com/vv/newsimg/15/06/zuk-smartphone/gsmarena_001.jpg" alt="" width="580" height="326" />', 'Lenovo''s Zuk Z1', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lenovos-zuk-z1', '', '', '2015-08-14 10:46:09', '2015-08-14 05:16:09', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=226', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(69, 1, '2015-07-14 20:08:23', '2015-07-14 14:38:23', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.samsung.com/in/consumer-images/product/mobile-phone/2015/SM-G920IZDAINS/features/SM-G920IZDAINS-403979-2.jpg" alt="" width="773" height="413" />\r\n\r\nHave you just purchased the new Samsung Galaxy S6? Are you looking for a way to root it, in order to install custom ROM’s or get rid of the bloatwares? Here is the ultimate guide to root the new Samsung Galaxy S6 smartphone:-\r\n\r\nWarning- Rooting your Samsung Smartphone will void its warranty and you won’t be able to claim it. Also, if you don’t follow the rooting steps properly, then there are chances of your device getting bricked. So, if anything goes wrong or if any damage is caused to your device while following this tutorial, do not held me or The Tech Log responsible. Proceed at your own risk.\r\n<h2>Requirements prior to the tutorial:</h2>\r\n1) This procedure is not a data loss procedure, but it is highly recommended to backup your smartphone to be on the safer side.\r\n\r\n2) Now enable USB Debugging mode in your smartphone. To do this, first you will have to enable Developer options by following, in order to do it follow these steps : <strong>Settings -&gt; About Phone</strong> (tap on the build number for 7 times to enable Developer Options). Now follow these steps to enable USB Debugging: <strong>Settings -&gt; Developer Options -&gt; USB Debugging</strong>.\r\n\r\n3) Your smartphone should have minimum 70% battery.\r\n\r\n4) Downlaod your smartphone’s drivers from this link: <a href="http://www.samsung.com/in/support/usefulsoftware/KIES/">http://www.samsung.com/in/support/usefulsoftware/KIES/</a>\r\n\r\n5)Disable antivirus temporarily.\r\n<h1><strong>Tutorial:</strong></h1>\r\n1) Make sure that your Galaxy 6 model number is SM-G920F or SM-G920T.\r\n\r\n2) Next, download Odin (<a href="http://d-h.st/users/Droidviews/?fld_id=40163#files">http://d-h.st/users/Droidviews/?fld_id=40163#files</a> ) and CF-Auto-Root-zeroflte-zerofltexx-smg920f (<a href="https://download.chainfire.eu/733/CF-Root/CF-Auto-Root/CF-Auto-Root-zeroflte-zerofltexx-smg920f.zip">https://download.chainfire.eu/733/CF-Root/CF-Auto-Root/CF-Auto-Root-zeroflte-zerofltexx-smg920f.zip</a> ) for SM-G920F or CF-Auto-Root/CF-Auto-Root-zerofltetmo-zerofltetmo-smg920t (<a href="https://download.chainfire.eu/731/CF-Root/CF-Auto-Root/CF-Auto-Root-zerofltetmo-zerofltetmo-smg920t.zip">https://download.chainfire.eu/731/CF-Root/CF-Auto-Root/CF-Auto-Root-zerofltetmo-zerofltetmo-smg920t.zip</a> ) for SM-G920T device to your system. Now, extract the CF Auto Root file and save the extracted .tar.md5 file in your system.\r\n\r\n3) Now, open Odin in your computer and switch off your Galaxy S6 device. To boot into the download mode press the Volume Down, Power and Home Buttons together.\r\n\r\n4) After you are in Download mode, connect your smartphone to the computer using the USB cable. Your device will be connected successfully if you have installed the driver properly earlier.\r\n\r\n5) Now in Odin, click on the AP button and choose the .tar.md5 file from the first step. Make sure that F.Reset Time and Auto-reboot options are selected and the Repartition button is unselected.\r\n\r\n6) Click Start in Odin to begin the process. It will take few minutes to get completed and once it is done, you will see a PASS message in Odin and your device will get rebooted. Once you see the Home screen of your smartphone, you can disconnect the device from the computer.\r\n\r\nIf all goes well you have successfully rooted your Samsung Galaxy S3 SM-920F. Just incase you encounter any problem comment in the section down below:\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://www.samsung.com/in/consumer-images/product/mobile-phone/2015/SM-G920IZDAINS/features/SM-G920IZDAINS-403979-2.jpg)', 'How to root Samsung Galaxy S6 smartphone', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-root-samsung-galaxy-s6-smartphone', '', '', '2015-07-15 10:08:40', '2015-07-15 04:38:40', 