-zeroflte-zerofltexx-smg920f (<a href="https://download.chainfire.eu/733/CF-Root/CF-Auto-Root/CF-Auto-Root-zeroflte-zerofltexx-smg920f.zip">https://download.chainfire.eu/733/CF-Root/CF-Auto-Root/CF-Auto-Root-zeroflte-zerofltexx-smg920f.zip</a> ) for SM-G920F or CF-Auto-Root/CF-Auto-Root-zerofltetmo-zerofltetmo-smg920t (<a href="https://download.chainfire.eu/731/CF-Root/CF-Auto-Root/CF-Auto-Root-zerofltetmo-zerofltetmo-smg920t.zip">https://download.chainfire.eu/731/CF-Root/CF-Auto-Root/CF-Auto-Root-zerofltetmo-zerofltetmo-smg920t.zip</a> ) for SM-G920T device to your system. Now, extract the CF Auto Root file and save the extracted .tar.md5 file in your system.\r\n\r\n3) Now, open Odin in your computer and switch off your Galaxy S6 device. To boot into the download mode press the Volume Down, Power and Home Buttons together.\r\n\r\n4) After you are in Download mode, connect your smartphone to the computer using the USB cable. Your device will be connected successfully if you have installed the driver properly earlier.\r\n\r\n5) Now in Odin, click on the AP button and choose the .tar.md5 file from the first step. Make sure that F.Reset Time and Auto-reboot options are selected and the Repartition button is unselected.\r\n\r\n6) Click Start in Odin to begin the process. It will take few minutes to get completed and once it is done, you will see a PASS message in Odin and your device will get rebooted. Once you see the Home screen of your smartphone, you can disconnect the device from the computer.\r\n\r\nIf all goes well you have successfully rooted your Samsung Galaxy S3 SM-920F. Just incase you encounter any problem comment in the section down below:\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://www.samsung.com/in/consumer-images/product/mobile-phone/2015/SM-G920IZDAINS/features/SM-G920IZDAINS-403979-2.jpg)', 'How to root Samsung Galaxy S6 smartphone', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '69-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-15 10:08:40', '2015-07-15 04:38:40', '', 69, 'http://thetechlog