(116, 1, '2015-07-18 11:52:00', '2015-07-18 06:22:00', '<img class="alignnone" src="https://cdn-blog.jolla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Sailfish2_Leaflet_wide-1024x479.jpg" alt="" width="815" height="381" />\r\n\r\nIndian smartphone manufacturer Intex recently became the first OEM partner for the Finnish operating system maker Jolla. Yesterday, Intex announced its new device Aqua fish at MWC, Shanghai .It plans to launch the device globally, but as of now it will be released only in India by November. It will be priced below Rs.10,000. The upcoming device will run on Sailfish 2.0 64- bit operating system (Under development). Sailfish OS is a linux based mobile operating system released in 2013 (Current version: 1.1.6.27 released on June 15, 2015) . It will support 4G as well.\r\n\r\nAccording to the company “The aim for Sailfish India is to develop a unique Indian mobile ecosystem, which will lead to greater differentiation in the market with more choices for consumers, higher user satisfaction and better revenues for local businesses. Further Sailfish India partners will be announced later.” Antii Saarnio (Executive Chairman and CEO ) added “We have seen a lot of interest among Indian device vendors, digital media houses, and mobile operators, and they all are very keen to work with an alternative to the currently dominating mobile operating systems. India deserves its own regional mobile ecosystem, an open platform, which supports local Indian services and businesses.”\r\n\r\nMoreover, it was last week when Jolla announced stepping back from manufacturing its devices itself. They plan to fully focus on the software upgrades and also setting up another company to manage its hardware in near future.\r\n\r\n(Image source- https://cdn-blog.jolla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Sailfish2_Leaflet_wide-1024x479.jpg\r\n\r\nhttps://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d3/Sailfish_logo.svg/1280px-Sailfish_logo.svg.png)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/j2TnTbShEwA" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d3/Sailfish_logo.svg/1280px-Sailfish_logo.svg.png" alt="" width="807" height="360" />', 'Intex Aqua, first Sailfish OS 2.0 device', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'intex-aqua-first-sailfish-os-2-0-device', '', '', '2015-07-18 11:57:04', '2015-07-18 06:27:04', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=116', 0, 'post', '', 0),
