(131, 1, '2015-07-20 16:33:32', '2015-07-20 11:03:32', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/marshall-london-phone-1_1900.jpg" alt="" width="819" height="546" />\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://icdn8.digitaltrends.com/image/marshall-london-17-970x647-c.jpg" alt="" width="818" height="546" />\r\n\r\nMarshall, a brand known for its famous guitar amplifiers announced its first smartphone "London" powered by android. Crazy right? Its not just a normal smartphone but an absolute melody for the music lovers. It has a beautiful body design and comes with two audio output ports with separate volume rockers. It has two front stereo speakers . It has a high quality audio processing unit "Wolfson WM8281 digital-analogue converter" on board. It has been priced at SEK 4,995 (Rs. 37,000 approximately).\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en">\r\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en">Change the way you listen to music. Marshall London. Pre-order now at <a href="http://t.co/ydQ22EjT83">http://t.co/ydQ22EjT83</a><a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/MarshallPhone?src=hash">#MarshallPhone</a><a href="http://t.co/wX0D1DR9SR">pic.twitter.com/wX0D1DR9SR</a></p>\r\n— Marshall Amps (@MarshallAmpsUK) <a href="https://twitter.com/MarshallAmpsUK/status/621976432399491072">July 17, 2015</a></blockquote>\r\nIt is currently available for pre-orders and is expected to be delivered by August. Its specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 5.0.2 (Lollipop)\r\n\r\n*4.7-inch 720p screen (Corning Gorilla Glass 3)\r\n\r\n* 16GB of Internal storage\r\n\r\n*1.2 Ghz Qualcomm Snapdragon 410\r\n\r\n*2GB RAM\r\n\r\n*8MP primary camera and 2MP front camera\r\n\r\n*2500mAh Battery\r\n\r\n* Dimensions: 149.40 x 74.70 x 9.80 and weighs 145\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/marshall-london-phone-1_1900.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://www9.pcmag.com/media/images/472079-marshall-london-smartphone.jpg?thumb=y\r\n\r\nhttp://icdn8.digita