(147, 1, '2015-07-24 10:00:50', '2015-07-24 04:30:50', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://news.highonandroid.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/05/Moto-X-3rd-generation.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="400" />\r\n\r\nLenovo owned company Motorola''s upcoming device Moto X (Gen 3) is expected to be launched on the 28th of July. And before the big launch event some of its pictures got leaked on the Android Peru Facebook page on Wednesday.  These pictures seem legit enough:\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Moto-X-3rd-Gen-leak.jpg" alt="" width="732" height="585" />\r\n\r\nAccording to the rumors, the device is said to include a a fingerprint scanner and its specifications are as following :-\r\n\r\n*Android 5.1.1 (Lollipop)\r\n\r\n*5.64-Inch QHD (1440x2560 pixels) Display\r\n\r\n*1.7GHz Quad-core processor\r\n\r\n*32GB Inbuilt storage (Expandable upto 128GB)\r\n\r\n*2070mAh Battery\r\n\r\n*Type C USB port\r\n\r\n*Dimensions: 41.5x70.7x11mm and weigh 149 g\r\n\r\nIt is expected to be priced at CHF 235 (Rs. 15,500).\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://www.androidcentral.com/sites/androidcentral.com/files/styles/larger/public/article_images/2015/07/alleged-moto-x-2015-leak-2.jpg?itok=IQfSuWAc\r\n\r\nhttp://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Moto-X-3rd-Gen-leak.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://news.highonandroid.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/05/Moto-X-3rd-generation.jpg)\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.androidcentral.com/sites/androidcentral.com/files/styles/larger/public/article_images/2015/07/alleged-moto-x-2015-leak-2.jpg?itok=IQfSuWAc" alt="" width="733" height="651" />', 'Moto X (Gen 3) leaked', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'moto-x-gen-3-leaked', '', '', '2015-07-23 22:55:14', '2015-07-23 17:25:14', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=147', 0, 'post', '', 0),
