(166, 1, '2015-07-28 10:39:09', '2015-07-28 05:09:09', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://stech3.firstpost.com/tech2images/640x359/proportional/jpeg/2015/07/oneplus2-624x351.jpg" alt="" width="638" height="359" />\r\n\r\nOnePlus today launched its 2016 flagship killer device "Two". The OnePlus Two will be available in India, US, Canada, EU and China on August 11. It has been priced at Rs 22,999 for 16GB variant and Rs 24,999 for 64GB variant. It comes with four StyleSwap covers  Bamboo, Black Apricot, Rosewood and Kevlar. It also comes with a fingerprint scanner and a USB Type-C port.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en">\r\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en">Presenting the 2016 Flagship Killer: <a href="http://t.co/rO5ZzhJodi">http://t.co/rO5ZzhJodi</a> <a href="http://t.co/t5um2oa01m">pic.twitter.com/t5um2oa01m</a></p>\r\n— OnePlus (@oneplus) <a href="https://twitter.com/oneplus/status/625865135358283776">July 28, 2015</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/UATpMHitrA0" width="690" height="415" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.androidcentral.com/sites/androidcentral.com/files/styles/xlarge_wm_brw/public/article_images/2015/07/oneplus-2-multi-colors.jpg?itok=K0Yscr0p" alt="" width="705" height="529" />\r\n\r\n<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0beQH0UdfFQ" width="690" height="415" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIts specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 5.1 (Oxygen OS)\r\n\r\n*5.5-inch IPS LCD at 1920x1080 (Gorilla Glass)\r\n\r\n*1.8GHz Snapdragon 810 processor\r\n\r\n*64GB variant with 4GB RAM and 16GB variant with 3GB RAM\r\n\r\n*3300 mAh Battery\r\n\r\n*Dimensions:152.9 x 75.9 x 8.9 mm and weighs 166g\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://tech.firstpost.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/oneplus_2.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://stech3.firstpost.com/tech2images/640x359/proportional/jpeg/2015/07/oneplus2-624x351.jpg)\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://tech.firstpost.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/oneplus_2.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="461" />', 'OnePlus Two launched', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oneplus-two-launched', '', '', '2015-07-28 10:39:51', '2015-07-28 05:09:51', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=166', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(167, 1, '2015-07-28 10:38:53', '2015-07-28 05:08:53', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/micromax_canvas_xpress_2.jpg" alt="" width="635" height="475" />\r\n\r\nMicromax yesterday launched its new smartphone "Canvas Xpress 2" in India. It has been priced at Rs. 5,999 and will be exclusively available on Flipkart. It will be available in Jet Black finish with a gold rim on the sides. Its first flash sale will be on August 4 at 2pm IST. It comes bundled with Vodafone''s free 500MB 3G data offer for 2 months. Its specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 4.4.2 KitKat\r\n\r\n*5-inch HD (720x1280 pixels) IPS display (Corning Gorilla Glass 3)\r\n\r\n*1.4GHz Octa-core MediaTek (MT6592M) processor\r\n\r\n*1GB RAM\r\n\r\n*8GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 32GB)\r\n\r\n*13MP Rear camera (OV sensor, 5P Largan Lens, Blue Glass filter and dual-LED flash) and 2MP front camera\r\n\r\n*2500mAh Battery\r\n\r\nAccording to Shubhajit Sen (CMO, Micromax Informatics Ltd.)"We are today proud to announce the launch of Micromax Canvas Xpress 2 - the most affordable octa-core smartphone in the market. This move will further consolidate our position as the clear market leader in the sub Rs. 7,500 category. We will continue to disrupt the market with similar innovations in collaboration with strategic partners like Flipkart; to keep achieving our mission of democratizing technology for the masses."\r\n\r\nAmitesh Jha (VP - Retail, Flipkart), "We are happy to launch Micromax''s latest - Canvas Xpress 2 as a Flipkart exclusive. Offering a new smartphone packed with exciting features and a powerful processor to our shoppers, we are confident that this product will resonate with our young customers."\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Micromax-Canvas-Xpress-2-E3131.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/micromax_canvas_xpress_2.jpg)\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Micromax-Canvas-Xpress-2-E3131.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="940" />', 'Micromax Canvas Xpress 2', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'micromax-canvas-xpress-2', '', '', '2015-07-28 10:40:52', '2015-07-28 05:10:52', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=167', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(168, 1, '2015-07-28 10:38:53', '2015-07-28 05:08:53', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/micromax_canvas_xpress_2.jpg" alt="" width="635" height="475" />\r\n\r\nMicromax yesterday launched its new smartphone "Canvas Xpress" in India. It has been priced at Rs. 5,999 and will be exclusively available on Flipkart. It will be available in Jet Black finish with a gold rim on the sides. Its first flash sale will be on August 4 at 2pm IST. It comes bundled with Vodafone''s free 500MB 3G data offer for 2 months. Its specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 4.4.2 KitKat\r\n\r\n*5-inch HD (720x1280 pixels) IPS display (Corning Gorilla Glass 3)\r\n\r\n*1.4GHz Octa-core MediaTek (MT6592M) processor\r\n\r\n*1GB RAM\r\n\r\n*8GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 32GB)\r\n\r\n*13MP Rear camera (OV sensor, 5P Largan Lens, Blue Glass filter and dual-LED flash) and 2MP front camera\r\n\r\n*2500mAh Battery\r\n\r\nAccording to Shubhajit Sen (CMO, Micromax Informatics Ltd.)"We are today proud to announce the launch of Micromax Canvas Xpress 2 - the most affordable octa-core smartphone in the market. This move will further consolidate our position as the clear market leader in the sub Rs. 7,500 category. We will continue to disrupt the market with similar innovations in collaboration with strategic partners like Flipkart; to keep achieving our mission of democratizing technology for the masses."\r\n\r\nAmitesh Jha (VP - Retail, Flipkart), "We are happy to launch Micromax''s latest - Canvas Xpress 2 as a Flipkart exclusive. Offering a new smartphone packed with exciting features and a powerful processor to our shoppers, we are confident that this product will resonate with our young customers."\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Micromax-Canvas-Xpress-2-E3131.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/micromax_canvas_xpress_2.jpg)\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://images.fonearena.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Micromax-Canvas-Xpress-2-E3131.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="940" />', 'Micromax Canvas Xpress 2', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '167-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-28 10:38:53', '2015-07-28 05:08:53', '', 167, 'http://thetechlog.in/2015/07/28/167-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(169, 1, '2015-07-28 10:39:09', '2015-07-28 05:09:09', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://stech3.firstpost.com/tech2images/640x359/proportional/jpeg/2015/07/oneplus2-624x351.jpg" alt="" width="638" height="359" />\r\n\r\nOnePlus today launched its 2016 flagship killer device "Two". The OnePlus Two will be available in India, US, Canada, EU and China on August 11. It has been priced at Rs 22,999 for 16GB variant and Rs 24,999 for 64GB variant. It comes with four StyleSwap covers  Bamboo, Black Apricot, Rosewood and Kevlar. It also comes with a fingerprint scanner and a USB Type-C port.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en">\r\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en">Presenting the 2016 Flagship Killer: <a href="http://t.co/rO5ZzhJodi">http://t.co/rO5ZzhJodi</a> <a href="http://t.co/t5um2oa01m">pic.twitter.com/t5um2oa01m</a></p>\r\n— OnePlus (@oneplus) <a href="https://twitter.com/oneplus/status/625865135358283776">July 28, 2015</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" async="" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n\r\n<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/UATpMHitrA0" width="690" height="415" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.androidcentral.com/sites/androidcentral.com/files/styles/xlarge_wm_brw/public/article_images/2015/07/oneplus-2-multi-colors.jpg?itok=K0Yscr0p" alt="" width="705" height="529" />\r\n\r\n<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0beQH0UdfFQ" width="690" height="415" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIts specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 5.1 (Oxygen OS)\r\n\r\n*5.5-inch IPS LCD at 1920x1080 (Gorilla Glass)\r\n\r\n*1.8GHz Snapdragon 810 processor\r\n\r\n*64GB variant with 4GB RAM and 16GB variant with 3GB RAM\r\n\r\n*3300 mAh Battery\r\n\r\n*Dimensions:152.9 x 75.9 x 8.9 mm and weighs 166g\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://tech.firstpost.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/oneplus_2.jpg\r\n\r\nht