(188, 1, '2015-07-30 10:51:09', '2015-07-30 05:21:09', '<img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/49753110/1438090851/1500x500" alt="" width="852" height="284" />\r\n\r\nMotorola yesterday launched its 3 new third generation devices "Moto G, Moto X Style and Moto X Play". They''re mostly the improved versions of their previous generations.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" lang="en">\r\n<p dir="ltr" lang="en">Water-resistant. All-day battery. Customizable. Pure Android. <a href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/HelloMoto?src=hash">#HelloMoto</a><a href="http://t.co/TNQYGXSDR2">http://t.co/TNQYGXSDR2</a></p>\r\n— Motorola Mobility (@Motorola) <a href="https://twitter.com/Motorola/status/626034288413290496">July 28, 2015</a></blockquote>\r\nMoto G (Gen 3)\r\n\r\n*Android 5.1.1 Lollipop\r\n\r\n*720p 5-Inch display\r\n\r\n*1.4 GHz quad-core Snapdragon 410 processor\r\n\r\n*2GB RAM\r\n\r\n*8GB or 16GB of in-built storage\r\n\r\n*13MP rear camera and a 5MP front camera\r\n\r\n*2,470mAh Battery (Quick charging)\r\n\r\n*4G LTE\r\n\r\n*Moto Assist, Moto Display and Moto Actions\r\n\r\nIt has been priced at Rs. 11,999 for the 8GB variant and Rs. 12,999 for the 16GB variant and is exclusively available on Flipkart.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMoto X Style\r\n\r\n*Android 5.1.1 Lollipop\r\n\r\n*5.7-Inch Quad HD display\r\n\r\n*six-core Snapdragon 808 processor\r\n\r\n*3GB RAM\r\n\r\n*16GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 64GB)\r\n\r\n*21MP rear camera and a 5MP front camera (Dual LED flash)\r\n\r\n*3,000 mAh Battery\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMoto X Play\r\n\r\n*Android Lollipop 5.1.1\r\n\r\n*5.5-Inch 1080p display\r\n\r\n*1.7GHz Snapdragon 615 octa-core processor\r\n\r\n*2GB RAM\r\n\r\n*16GB or 32GB In-built storage\r\n\r\n*21MP rear camera and a 5MP front camera\r\n\r\n*3,630mAh Battery\r\n\r\n(Image source- https://twitter.com/Motorola)\r\n\r\n<img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/CLAWzgHWgAAWeSK.jpg" alt="Embedded image permalink" width="700" height="350