(197, 1, '2015-08-02 22:13:41', '2015-08-02 16:43:41', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://static.dnaindia.com/sites/default/files/2015/08/01/361107-lava-smartphone-iris-x1-selfie-530072015063918794.jpg" alt="" width="540" height="540" />\r\n\r\nLava recently launched its new selfie focused smartphone "Lava Iris X1 Selfie" in India. It has been priced at Rs. 6,777 and will go on sale from next week. It will be available in Icy White, Royal Black, and Purple color variants. Its specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n* Android 5.0 Lollipop\r\n\r\n*4.5-Inch FWVGA (854x480 pixels) IPS display\r\n\r\n*1.3GHz Quad-core MediaTek MT6580 processor\r\n\r\n*1GB DDR3 RAM\r\n\r\n*8MP rear camera and 5MP selfie front camera (LED flash)\r\n\r\n*8GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 32GB)\r\n\r\n*3G, Wi-Fi, USB 2.0, GPS, and Bluetooth\r\n\r\n*2000mAh Li-Po Battery\r\n\r\n*Dimensions: 133.5x66.0x8.5mm and weighs 140g\r\n\r\nAccording to Navin Chawla (Senior Vice President and Head - Product, Lava International Limited),"Keeping in line with the current trend and insights gathered from our young audience, we are excited to announce the launch of Iris X1 selfie, specially meant for selfie enthusiasts. We realize that there is a need for such devices and with our R&amp;D efforts this offering has a perfect combination of hardware and software driven front camera capabilities."\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Lava Iris X1 Selfie', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lava-iris-x1-selfie', '', '', '2015-08-02 22:13:41', '2015-08-02 16:43:41', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=197', 0, 'post', '', 0),
