(204, 1, '2015-08-04 11:30:27', '2015-08-04 06:00:27', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.static.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Xperia-C5-Ultra-and-M5_1-640x480.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="480" />\r\n\r\nSony yesterday launched its two new smartphones "Sony Xperia C5 Ultra and Xperia M5 Selfie". They''ll be available in both single SIM and dual SIM variants.\r\n\r\nXperia C5 Ultra\r\n\r\n*Android 5.0 Lollipop\r\n\r\n*6-Inch full-HD (1080x1920 pixels) IPS display (Bravia Engine 2)\r\n\r\n* 1.7 GHz 64-Bit octa-core MediaTek (MT6752) processor\r\n\r\n*ARM Mali760 GPU\r\n\r\n*2GB RAM\r\n\r\n*16GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 200GB)\r\n\r\n*13MP Front and rear camera\r\n\r\n* GPRS/ EDGE, GPS/ A-GPS, NFC, Glonass, Bluetooth, Wi-Fi, Micro-USB, 3G, and 4G LTE\r\n\r\n*2930mAh Battery\r\n\r\n*Dimensions:164.2x79.6x8.2mm and weighs 187g\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSony Xperia M5\r\n\r\n*Android 5.0 Lollipop\r\n\r\n*5-Inch full-HD (1080x1920 pixels) display\r\n\r\n*2GHz 64-bit octa-core MediaTek Helio X10 (MT6795) processor\r\n\r\n*3GB RAM\r\n\r\n*16GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 200GB)\r\n\r\n*21.5MP rear camera and a 13MP front camera (Hybrid autofocus)\r\n\r\n*GPRS/ EDGE, 3G, and 4G\r\n\r\n*2600mAh Battery\r\n\r\nAccording to Tony McNulty  (Vice-President, Value Category Business Management, Sony Mobile Communications),"We are pleased to present two new products that highlight Sony''s advances in camera technology. We understand that camera capabilities are important to smartphone users, so we ensured that Sony''s existing camera brilliance was once again surpassed in the new Xperia C5 Ultra and Xperia M5 without compromising on other features across design and performance."\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://www.static.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Xperia-C5-Ultra-and-M5_1-640x480.jpg)', 'Sony Xperia C5 Ultra and Xperia M5 Selfie', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sony-xperia-c5-ultra-and-xperia-m5-selfie', '', '', '2015-08-03 19:22:48', '20