(335, 1, '2015-09-09 23:54:21', '2015-09-09 18:24:21', 'Apple Special Event September 2015\r\n\r\nFrom Cupertino, California.\r\n\r\nLIVE NOW- Refresh for new updates or <a href="http://thetechlog.in/2015/09/09/apple-special-event-september-2015-live-blog/">Click here</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://images.apple.com/home/images/og.jpg?201507310104" alt="" width="280" height="280" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The event gets started at 22:30 IST on Wednesday, September 9th.</li>\r\n	<li>Good evening everyone! We''re blogging here live from Apple''s special event in the Bill Graham Civic auditorium, where the the new iPhone 6S is expected to be launched.</li>\r\n	<li>Apple''s apparently playing the Beats 1 Radio at the venue.</li>\r\n	<li>The auditorium is looking beautiful with the planetarium look!</li>\r\n	<li>Beats 1 is off now, And they''re playing "Dreams" by Beck.</li>\r\n	<li>Tim Cook is on the stage now.</li>\r\n	<li>"We''re so glad that so many people from all over the world could join us, including many of our employees."</li>\r\n	<li>"We are really firing on all cylinders, and we are about to make some monster announcements across several of our product lines."</li>\r\n	<li>"No time for updates, so I''d like to get right in and talk about Apple Watch."</li>\r\n	<li>"Customer satisfaction is an incredible 97 percent."</li>\r\n	<li>"We are on an incredible pace of innovation, and to tell you about where we''re going next, I''d like to invite Jeff Williams to the stage."</li>\r\n	<li>Jeff Williams is on the stage now.</li>\r\n	<li>"Third-party complications are a really big deal... you can see things like the latest news and airline departures."</li>\r\n	<li>"There are already over 10,000 Watch apps on the App Store. And now with native apps developers can do even more."</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21204/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0194.jpg" alt="" width="611" height="408" /></li>\r\n	<li>"The wrist is an ideal location to control your GoPro, and now the Watch is your viewfinder."</li>\r\n	<li>Airstrip demo by Dr. Cameron Powell.</li>\r\n	<li>"Let''s talk about how AirStrip with Apple Watch will change how doctors interact with their patients."</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21211/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0269.jpg" alt="" width="610" height="407" /></li>\r\n	<li>Jeff Williams is back on the stage.</li>\r\n	<li>"We think the power and potential of Watch OS is unlimited"</li>\r\n	<li>Apple has been working with Hermes.</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21216/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0326.jpg" alt="" width="610" height="407" /></li>\r\n	<li>"We''ve been working on new models and new bands, and we''d like to show them to you now."</li>\r\n	<li>New colors, same price! Gold and Rose Gold in anodized aluminum.</li>\r\n	<li>Tim Cook is back on the stage.</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21223/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0428.jpg" alt="" width="613" height="409" /></li>\r\n	<li>"Next up is iPad"</li>\r\n	<li>"iPad is the ultimate expression of our vision of the future of computing."</li>\r\n	<li>"We''ve been amazed with the new and unexpected things people have done with the iPad, so we asked ourselves how can we take the iPad even further?"</li>\r\n	<li>"The biggest news in iPad since iPad."</li>\r\n	<li>iPad Pro is here! It''s Huge!</li>\r\n	<li>"This is the iPad Pro. It''s the most capable and powerful iPad we''ve ever created. It is chock full of amazing technologies and innovations."</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21230/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0550.jpg" alt="" width="618" height="412" /></li>\r\n	<li>"Biggest screen on an iOS device, more power and performance than any iOS device."</li>\r\n	<li>Phil Schiller is on the stage now.</li>\r\n	<li>"Why make a bigger display? It''s a magical piece of glass that lets you touch the software. It can do things that a smartphone can''t do, because it doesn''t have to fit in your pocket, and it can do things a laptop can''t do because you can hold it all day."</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21235/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0605.jpg" alt="" width="616" height="411" /></li>\r\n	<li>"The most advanced display we''ve ever built."</li>\r\n	<li>5.6 Million pixels.</li>\r\n	<li>A9X chip, with 2x memory bandwidth and 2x storage performance.</li>\r\n	<li>"Desktop-class performance."</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21241/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0671.jpg" alt="" width="620" height="414" /></li>\r\n	<li>"iPad Pro is fater than 80 percent of the PCs that shipped in the past six months, and graphics are faster than 90 percent of those PCs."</li>\r\n	<li>Auto CAD demo</li>\r\n	<li>10 Hours battery life.</li>\r\n	<li>It will have 4 audio speaker system.</li>\r\n	<li>"We thought this display deserves a great sound system." Four-speaker audio system that balances stereo and frequencies depending on how you hold it.</li>\r\n	<li>"6.9mm thick compared to 6.1mm for the Air 2."</li>\r\n	<li>1.57 pounds.</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21248/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0743.jpg" alt="" width="627" height="419" /></li>\r\n	<li>"Sometimes you want the convenience of a physical keyboard." A new Smart Keyboard accessory.</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21249/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0752.jpg" alt="" width="633" height="422" /></li>\r\n	<li>"A "woven fabric" creates the strucutre of the keys."</li>\r\n	<li>"There''s a new connector on the side of the iPad Pro called the Smart Connecter; it carries power and data to the keyboard."</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21251/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0776.jpg" alt="" width="631" height="421" /></li>\r\n	<li>"We will continute to use our hands to interact in amazing ways with iPad."</li>\r\n	<li>Stylus is here!</li>\r\n	<li>Apple Pencil</li>\r\n	<li>"Touch, of course, is the primary method of input with the iPad."</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21254/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0824.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="427" /></li>\r\n	<li>"We''ve designed Apple Pencil, this began by reengineering the display."</li>\r\n	<li>"Highly responsive sensors built into the tip of Apple Pencil sensor pressure, tilt, and stroke."</li>\r\n	<li>"Its unique tip signature allows it to be used simultaneously with your finger."</li>\r\n	<li>"Apple Pencil is designed to look and feel like a familiar tool."</li>\r\n	<li>"New Notes app where you can draw and diagram directly with Apple Pencil."</li>\r\n	<li>"Who better to work with us on productivity than Microsoft?"</li>\r\n	<li>Kirk Konigsbauer from the Microsoft Office team on stage.</li>\r\n	<li>"Today more than ever we are supporting Microsoft Office on Apple platforms."</li>\r\n	<li>"With Office for iPad, we want to make it easier than ever to make rich documents with touch."</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21265/apple-iphone-6s-live-_0971.jpg" alt="" width="644" height="429" /></li>\r\n	<li>Eric Snowden from Adobe is on the stage now.</li>\r\n	<li>He''s giving a demo of their new iPad apps.</li>\r\n	<li>Adobe Photoshop Sketch</li>\r\n	<li>Irene Walsh is on the stage now.</li>\r\n	<li>A new app called 3D4Medical has been introduced.</li>\r\n	<li>"I''m excited to show you how with the new iPad Pro, our ability to communicate with patients has dramatically improved."</li>\r\n	<li>Schiller is back on the stage.</li>\r\n	<li>"This is the most advanced iPad we''ve made ever."</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21278/apple-iphone-6s-live-_1121.jpg" alt="" width="652" height="435" /></li>\r\n	<li>"Up to 150 Mbps LTE."</li>\r\n	<li>It will be available in Space Gray, Gold and Silver colors. Starts at $799 and goes to $1079.</li>\r\n	<li>Apple Pencil is $99 and Smart Keyboard is $169, all will be available in November.</li>\r\n	<li>They''re showing a video now.</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21289/apple-iphone-6s-live-_1232.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="434" /></li>\r\n	<li>Its time for the new Apple TV.</li>\r\n	<li>"It''s the golden age of televisions."</li>\r\n	<li>"The television experience has been virtually standing still while innovation in the mobile space has been racing ahead. Today, we are going to do something about that."</li>\r\n	<li>"Our vision for TV is simple and perhaps a little provocative. We believe the future of telebision is apps."</li>\r\n	<li>"This transition has already begun. Over 60 percent of pay TV streaming video is consumed on an Apple device, through an app."</li>\r\n	<li>The future of TV is apps.</li>\r\n	<li>"When you consume this way, you realize just how much better it can be."</li>\r\n	<li>"To deliver on this vision, we need a new foundation for TV, built on powerful hardware, that runs a modern opererating system, with a new user experience, great developer tools, and of course an App Store."</li>\r\n	<li>"We know this is what it takes, and we''ve been working really hard and really long to bring all of these together."</li>\r\n	<li>"Today I''m thrilled to show you the new Apple TV." Video time!</li>\r\n	<li>The remote seems to have a touchpad.</li>\r\n	<li>"We''ve been working really hard, and really long"</li>\r\n	<li>Eddy Cue is on the stage now.</li>\r\n	<li>They''re playing a video now</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21299/apple-iphone-6s-live-_1343.jpg" alt="" width="654" height="436" /></li>\r\n	<li>He''s giving a demo.</li>\r\n	<li>It now has universal search.</li>\r\n	<li>Cue is back. "Apple has redesigned all its apps."</li>\r\n	<li>tvOS is here.</li>\r\n	<li>Game demo: Hipster Whale''s Crossy Road.</li>\r\n	<li>Few more demos.</li>\r\n	<li>TV OS has notifications.</li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21345/apple-iphone-6s-live-_1759.jpg" alt="" width="655" height="437" /></li>\r\n	<li><img class="" src="http://d35lb3dl296zwu.cloudfront.net/uploads/photo/image/21347/apple-iphone-6s-live-_1772.jpg" alt="" width="654" height="436" /></li>\r\n	<li>It will be available in late October.</li>\r\n	<li>Its time for iPhone!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://thetechlog.in/2015/09/09/apple-special-event-september-2015-live-blog/">Click here</a> for new update.\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://images.apple.com/home/images/og.jpg?201507310104\r\n\r\nwww.theverge.com)', 'Apple Special Event September 2015 - Live Blog', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '276-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-09 23:54:21', '2015-09-09 18:24:21', '', 276, 'http://thetechlog.in/2015/09/09/276-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
