(351, 1, '2015-09-14 00:43:50', '2015-09-13 19:13:50', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.timesnews.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/YU-Yunique-Snapdeal.jpg" alt="" width="515" height="406" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMicromax''s Yu recently launched its new device "Yunique" in India. It has been priced at Rs.4999 and will be exclusively available on Snapdeal. Its flash sale will be held on 15th September at 12:00 PM. Its specifications are as following:-\r\n\r\n*Android 5.1.1 Lollipop (Cyanogen OS 12.1)\r\n\r\n*4.7-Inch HD (720x1280 pixels) resolution display (312ppi)\r\n\r\n*1.2Ghz 64-Bit quad-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 410 processor\r\n\r\n*1GB LPDDR3 RAM\r\n\r\n*8GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 32GB)\r\n\r\n*8MP Rear camera 2MP front camera\r\n\r\n*4G LTE,Wi-Fi, Wi-Fi hotspot, GPS, A-GPS, Bluetooth 4.0, FM radio and Micro-USB v2.0\r\n\r\n*2000mAh Battery\r\n\r\nAccording to Rahul Sharma (Founder, YU Televentures), "India is at the tipping point of digital revolution and we expect 4G technology to push Internet usage to an unprecedented level. Consumer demand is constantly shifting towards devices offering multi-tasking capabilities, 24x7 data connectivity with increased video consumption and real-time mobility solutions. However to boost adoption, 3 key things including price, product and reach are important. I feel that with Yunique being available at 4,999 through a partner like Snapdeal that has the farthest reach, we have a compelling preposition to delight the consumer."\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n(Image Source-http://www.timesnews.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/YU-Yunique-Snapdeal.jpg)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Yu Yunique', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '349-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 00:43:50', '2015-09-13 19:13:50', '', 349, 'http://thetechlog.in/2015/09/14/349-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
