(385, 1, '2015-10-05 08:33:25', '2015-10-05 03:03:25', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/micromax_bolt_q339_front.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="600" />\r\n\r\nMicromax recently launched its new smartphone "Bolt Q339" in India. It has been priced at Rs. 3,499 and will exclusively be available on Flipkart. Vodafone India is offering 500 MB of 3G data free for 2 months bundled along with this smartphone. Its specifications are as following:-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Android 4.4.2 KitKat</li>\r\n	<li>4.5-Inch (480x854 pixels) FWVGA IPS display</li>\r\n	<li>1.2GHz Quad-core Spreadtrum (SC7731) processor</li>\r\n	<li>512MB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>4GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 32GB)</li>\r\n	<li>5MP Rear camera and a 2MP front camera</li>\r\n	<li>3G, GPRS/ EDGE, Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, Micro-USB and Bluetooth</li>\r\n	<li>1650mAh Battery</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions: 123x63.8x9.7mm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAccording to Vineet Taneja (CEO, Micromax),"Created for the discerning Indian consumer, the Bolt Q339 has been launched, this festive season, to empower a wider consumer base with the experience of best-in-class mobile technologies and richer on-the-go internet experience at an affordable price. Bolt Q339 is one of the most affordable 4.5-inch, 3G quad-core devices in the Indian market. We believe that the new offering being available through Flipkart that has a reach across the length and breadth of the country, coupled with Micromax''s trusted product quality and after-sales service track record, creates a compelling proposition to delight the Indian consumer."\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/micromax_bolt_q339_front.jpg)', 'Micromax Bolt Q339', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'micromax-bolt-q339', '', '', '2015-10-05 08:34:27', '2015-10-05 03:04:27', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=385', 0, 'post', '', 2),
