(388, 1, '2015-10-06 08:08:35', '2015-10-06 02:38:35', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cnet3.cbsistatic.com/hub/i/r/2015/09/02/1d221075-66bf-4877-abfe-6aad889bd2ed/resize/1170xauto/a8af4a29dac9fb4dc39ebd97e3a7ddce/lenovo-phab-plus.jpg" alt="" width="753" height="501" />\r\n\r\nLenovo last week launched its new smartphone "Phab Plus" in India. It has been priced at Rs. 20,990 and is currently available on Amazon for Rs. 18,490.It is available in is available in Gunmetal Platinum color variant. Its specifications are as following:-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Android 5.0 Lollipop (Vibe UI)</li>\r\n	<li>6.8-Inch full-HD (1080x1920 pixels) display</li>\r\n	<li>1.5GHz 64-Bit octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 615 processor</li>\r\n	<li>2GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>32GB In-built storage (Expandable)</li>\r\n	<li>Adreno 405 GPU</li>\r\n	<li>13MP Rear camera and a 5MP front camera</li>\r\n	<li>4G, 3G, GPS/ A-GPS, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth and Micro-USB</li>\r\n	<li>3500mAh Battery</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions: 186.6x96.6x7.6mm and weighs 220g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAccording to Rohit Midha (Director ,Tablet Business Unit, Lenovo India),"The smartphone has become an integral companion for most of us, fitting into all aspects of our lives. As we strive to do more and achieve more, the Phab Plus is a smart device designed to live up to users on all counts, making life more convenient especially owing to its impressive screen size. The Lenovo Phab Plus truly combines the awesomeness of a phone and a tablet in one cool device."\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://cnet3.cbsistatic.com/hub/i/r/2015/09/02/1d221075-66bf-4877-abfe-6aad889bd2ed/resize/1170xauto/a8af4a29dac9fb4dc39ebd97e3a7ddce/lenovo-phab-plus.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://www.androidcentral.com/sites/androidcentral.com/files/styles/larger/public/article_images/2015/08/lenovo-phab-03.jpg?itok=vifLghjV)\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.androidcentral.com/sites/androidcentral.com/files/styles/larger/public/article_images/2015/08/lenovo-phab-03.jpg?itok=vifLghjV" alt