(394, 1, '2015-10-07 21:21:41', '2015-10-07 15:51:41', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://crackberry.com/sites/crackberry.com/files/styles/larger/public/article_images/2015/09/Render-BB-Priv.png" alt="" width="774" height="516" />\r\n\r\nBlackberry recently announced its upcoming new Android slider smartphone “Priv”. It features a slider QWERTY keyboard. Blackberry admitted that BB OS 10 lacked many applications and wasn’t able to attract people towards itself. So, now Blackberry aims at bringing people back to its platform by introducing Android to its devices. Confirming the rumored specifications the final release will support:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Android 5.0 Lollipop</li>\r\n	<li>4-Inch QHD (1440x2560 pixels) display</li>\r\n	<li>1.8GHz Hexa-core 64-bit Snapdragon 808 processor</li>\r\n	<li>3GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>18MP Rear camera and 5MP front camera</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe release date for this device hasn’t been announced yet.\r\n\r\n(Image source-http://crackberry.com/sites/crackberry.com/files/styles/larger/public/article_images/2015/09/Render-BB-Priv.png)', 'Blackberry Priv announced', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '381-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-10-07 21:21:41', '2015-10-07 15:51:41', '', 381, 'http://thetechlog.in/2015/10/07/381-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(395, 1, '2015-10-07 21:22:08', '2015-10-07 15:52:08', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.gsmarena.com/imgroot/reviews/15/microsoft-lumia-event/lifestyle/-728w2/gsmarena_001.jpg" alt="" width="728" height="314" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWith Microsoft claiming over 110 million devices which are already running the new Windows 10, it has been a very great start of the quarter for the tech giant. Yesterday, Microsoft announced some fresh devices, which are honestly INCREDIBLE. Cutting the intro short here is the list of the amazing-ly new hardware from Microsoft:\r\n<h1><img class="alignnone" src="http://core0.staticworld.net/images/article/2015/10/surface-book-front-back-100620178-orig.png" alt="" width="780" height="415" /></h1>\r\n<h1>Surface Book</h1>\r\nWhat? Book? A laptop? YES! Microsoft has finally released its new laptop, First in its series and it looks crazy! It comes in a silver colored magnesium casing ( Whatsup? MacBook Air?) with a 13.5-inch screen (267 ppi). It has a detachable keyboard and hence, can be used as a tablet or a laptop. Its dimensions are 12.30x 9.14x 0.51-0.90 inches and it weighs over 1,516g. Its specifications are as following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>SSD options of 128GB, 256GB, 512GB, or 1TB</li>\r\n	<li>6th Gen Intel Core i5 or i7</li>\r\n	<li>Graphics:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>i5: Intel HD graphics 520</li>\r\n	<li>i5/i7: NVIDIA GeForce Graphics Processor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>8GB or 16GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>Windows 10 Pro</li>\r\n	<li>WiFi 802.11ac, Bluetooth 4</li>\r\n	<li>8MP Rear camera and a 5MP front camera</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIt has been priced at $1,499 and will be available from October 26.\r\n<h1><img class="alignnone" src="http://images.christianpost.com/full/86136/microsoft-surface-pro-4.png" alt="" width="560" height="280" /></h1>\r\n<h1>Surface Pro 4</h1>\r\nThe Surface Pro series has a successor now with Microsoft introducing the new "Surface Pro 4". It is 30% faster than Surface Pro 3 and 50% faster than MacBook Air. It also comes with an exterior magnesium casing and will be available in silver color. Its specifications are as following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Windows 10 Pro</li>\r\n	<li>Intel 6th Gen m3, i5, or i7 processors</li>\r\n	<li>4GB, 8GB, or 16GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>Graphics:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>m3: Intel HD graphics 515</li>\r\n	<li>i5: Intel HD graphics 520</li>\r\n	<li>i7: Intel Iris</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions: 11.50 x 7.93x 0.33 inch</li>\r\n	<li>SSD options:  128GB, 256GB, 512GB, or 1TB.</li>\r\n	<li>12.3-inch PixelTouch display (2736 x 1824 (267 PPI))</li>\r\n	<li>Wi-Fi 802.11ac and Bluetooth 4</li>\r\n	<li>8MP Rear camera and a 5MP front camera</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIt has been priced at:\r\n\r\nm3: $899\r\ni5:$999\r\ni7:$1599\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/images/gadgets/lumia_950_950_xl_microsoft_3.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="637" />\r\n<h1></h1>\r\n<h1></h1>\r\n<h1>Microsoft Lumia 950</h1>\r\n<ul class="article-blurb article-blurb-features">\r\n	<li>Windows 10 and Windows 10 Continuum ( via a dedicated dock which coverts your phone into a pocket PC)</li>\r\n	<li>5.2 Inch Quad HD AMOLED display (564ppi) (Gorilla Glass 4)</li>\r\n	<li>1.8 GHz Dual-core Cortex-A57 and a 1.4 GHz quad-core Cortex-A53 processor</li>\r\n	<li>Adreno 418 GPU</li>\r\n	<li>3GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>20MP Rear camera and  a 5MP front camera</li>\r\n	<li>32GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 200GB)</li>\r\n	<li>LTE Cat.4 (up to 150Mbps), Cat. 6 LTE (up to 300Mbps) and a USB Type C port</li>\r\n	<li>3000 mAh Battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1><img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/images/gadgets/windows_hello_continuum_microsoft_2.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="596" /></h1>\r\n<h1>Microsoft Lumia 950 XL</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Windows 10 and Windows 10 Continuum</li>\r\n	<li>5.7 Inch Quad HD AMOLED display (518ppi) (Gorilla Glass 3)</li>\r\n	<li>2 GHz quad-core Cortex-A57 and a 1.5 GHz quad-core Cortex-A53 processor</li>\r\n	<li>Adreno 430 GPU</li>\r\n	<li>3GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>20MP Rear camera and a 5MP front camera</li>\r\n	<li>32GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 200GB)</li>\r\n	<li>LTE Cat.4 (up to 150Mbps), Cat. 6 LTE (up to 300Mbps) and a USB Type C port</li>\r\n	<li>3300 mAh Battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1><img class="alignnone" src="https://cdn3.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/51agzqB9GKsTcFHozJ3CaWTt0aE=/800x0/filters:no_upscale()/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/4131104/Lumia-550.0.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="514" /></h1>\r\n<h1>Microsoft Lumia 550</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Windows 10</li>\r\n	<li>4.7 Inch 720p LCD display (316ppi)</li>\r\n	<li>1.1 GHz quad-core Cortex-A7 processor</li>\r\n	<li>Adreno 304 GPU</li>\r\n	<li>1GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>5MP Rear camera and a 2MP front camera</li>\r\n	<li>8GB In-built storage (Exapandable)</li>\r\n	<li>LTE Cat.4 (up to 150Mbps)</li>\r\n	<li>2100 mAh Battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n(Image source- http://cdn.gsmarena.com/imgroot/reviews/15/microsoft-lumia-event/lifestyle/-728w2/gsmarena_001.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://core0.staticworld.net/images/article/2015/10/surface-book-front-back-100620178-orig.png\r\n\r\nhttp://images.christianpost.com/full/86136/microsoft-surface-pro-4.png\r\n\r\nhttp://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/images/gadgets/lumia_950_950_xl_microsoft_3.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/images/gadgets/windows_hello_continuum_microsoft_2.jpg\r\n\r\nhttps://cdn3.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/51agzqB9GKsTcFHozJ3CaWTt0aE=/800x0/filters:no_upscale()/cdn0.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/4131104/Lumia-550.0.jpg)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Windows 10 Device Event - October 2015', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '391-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-10-07 21:22:08', '2015-10-07 15:52:08', '', 391, 'http://thetechlog.in/2015/10/07/391-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
