(471, 1, '2015-10-30 22:59:00', '2015-10-30 17:29:00', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn02.androidauthority.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/oneplus-2-launch-aa-46-of-931-840x473.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="473" />\r\n\r\nOnePlus recently launched its new smartphone "X" in India. It has been priced at Rs.16,999 for the Onyx variant and Rs.22,999 for the Ceramic variant. It will go on sale from November 5 and will be exclusively available on Amazon. Its specifications are as followings:-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Android 5.1.1 Lollipop (OxygenOS)</li>\r\n	<li>5-Inch full-HD (1080x1920 pixels) Amoled display</li>\r\n	<li>2.3GHz Quad-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 801 processor</li>\r\n	<li>3GB LPDDR3 RAM</li>\r\n	<li>16GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 128GB)</li>\r\n	<li>13MP Rear camera and a 8MP front camera</li>\r\n	<li>4G LTE ,Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, FM radio and Micro-USB</li>\r\n	<li>2525mAh Battery</li>\r\n	<li>Weight:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ceramic variant: 160g</li>\r\n	<li>Onyx variant: 138g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n(Image source- http://cdn02.androidauthority.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/oneplus-2-launch-aa-46-of-931-840x473.jpg)', 'OnePlus X', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oneplus-x', '', '', '2015-10-30 22:59:00', '2015-10-30 17:29:00', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=471', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(413, 1, '2015-10-14 18:54:41', '2015-10-14 13:24:41', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.themobileindian.com/images/new_launches/2015/10/5943/P65-Flash.jpg" alt="" width="950" height="550" />\r\n\r\nPanasonic recently launched its two new smartphones "P50 Idol and P65 Flash" in India. They have been priced at Rs. 6,790 and Rs. 8,290 respectively. Their specifications are as following:-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Android 5.1 Lollipop</li>\r\n	<li>Display:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Panasonic P50 Idol : 5-inch HD (720x1280 pixels) IPS display</li>\r\n	<li>Panasonic P65 Flash : 5.5-inch HD (720x1280 pixels) IPS display</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>1.3GHz Quad-core processor</li>\r\n	<li>1GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>8GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 32GB)</li>\r\n	<li>8MP Rear camera and a 2MP front camera</li>\r\n	<li> 3G, GPRS/ EDGE, Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, GPS/ A-GPS, Micro-USB and Bluetooth.</li>\r\n	<li>Battery:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>P50 Idol : 2150 mAh</li>\r\n	<li>P65 Flash : 2910 mAh</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions and weight:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>P50 Idol : 142x71.5x8.7mm and 139g</li>\r\n	<li>P65 Idol : 151x77.8x8.95mm and 168g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAccording to Pankaj Rana (Business Head, Mobility Division, Panasonic India), "With the release of the P50 Idol and P65 Flash, Panasonic now offers nearly 30 smartphones at affordable price points for every buyer to indulge themselves or their loved ones this festive season."\r\n\r\n(Image source- www.themobileindian.com/images/new_launches/2015/10/5943/P65-Flash.jpg)', 'Panasonic P50 Idol and P65 Flash', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'panasonic-p50-idol-and-p65-flash', '', '', '2015-10-14 23:19:01', '2015-10-14 17:49:01', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=413', 0, 'post', '', 0),
