(445, 1, '2015-10-18 10:51:00', '2015-10-18 05:21:00', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://www.themobileindian.com/images/new_launches/2015/10/5955/CLOUD-SWIFT.jpg" alt="" width="950" height="550" />\r\n\r\nIntex recently launched its new smartphone "Cloud swift" in India. It has been priced at Rs. 8,888 and will exclusively be available on Snapdeal from Tuesday. It will be available in Champagne and Grey color variants. Its specifications are as followings:-\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Android 5.1 Lollipop</li>\r\n	<li>5 Inch (720x1280 pixels) IPS display (320ppi)</li>\r\n	<li>1.3GHz Quad-core MediaTek MT6735A processor</li>\r\n	<li>3GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>16GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 128GB)</li>\r\n	<li>8MP Rear camera and a 5MP front camera</li>\r\n	<li>4G LTE, Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, Bluetooth 4.0, Micro-USB 2.0 and GPS/ A-GPS</li>\r\n	<li>2500mAh Battery</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions: 144.5x72.5x8.9mm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAccording to Sanjay Kumar Kalirona (Mobile Business Head, Intex Technologies), "Online space is clearly the central destination for next generation of consumers. Intex has launched a category defying product, Cloud Swift exclusively online. We are happy to partner with one of India''s leading e-commerce portal - Snapdeal and are sure that this exclusive association will offer consumers an unmatchable experience at a never before price-point."\r\n\r\n(Image source- http://www.themobileindian.com/images/new_launches/2015/10/5955/CLOUD-SWIFT.jpg)', 'Intex Cloud Swift', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'intex-cloud-swift', '', '', '2015-10-18 10:54:32', '2015-10-18 05:24:32', '', 0, 'http://thetechlog.in/?p=445', 0, 'post', '', 0),
