(460, 1, '2015-10-25 11:05:13', '2015-10-25 05:35:13', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/images/sony_xperia_z5_green.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="600" />\r\n\r\nSony on Wednesday launched its two new smartphones "Xperia Z5 and Xperia Z5 Premium Dual-SIM" in India. They have been priced at Rs. 52,990 and Rs. 62,990 respectively and will be available from 7th November. Their specifications are as followings:-\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><img class="alignnone" src="http://mobi.mobipicker.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/xperia-z5-series.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="450" /></h3>\r\n<h3>Sony Xperia Z5 Dual (Gold, Green and Black color variants) and Sony Xperia Z5 Premium Dual (Gold and Chrome color variants)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Android 5.1 Lollipop</li>\r\n	<li>Display:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sony Xperia Z5 Dual:  5.2-inch display</li>\r\n	<li>Sony Xperia Z5 Premium Dual:  5.5-inch display (2160x3840 pixels) (806ppi) (4K)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>64-Bit octa-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 810 processor</li>\r\n	<li>3GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>16GB In-built storage (Expandable upto 2TB)</li>\r\n	<li>23MP Rear camera (1/2.3-Inch Exmor RS) (F/2.0 G lens) and a 5MP front camera</li>\r\n	<li>Battery (Quick charge):\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sony Xperia Z5 Dual: 2900mAh battery</li>\r\n	<li>Sony Xperia Z5 Premium Dual: 3430mAh battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n(Image source- http://cdn2.pcadvisor.co.uk/cmsdata/reviews/3624456/Sony_Xperia_Z5_compared_review_82.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://mobi.mobipicker.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/xperia-z5-series.jpg\r\n\r\nhttp://cdn.ndtv.com/tech/images/sony_xperia_z5_green.jpg)\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone" src="http://cdn2.pcadvisor.co.uk/cmsdata/reviews/3624456/Sony_Xperia_Z5_compared_review_82.jpg" alt="" width="793" height="446" />', 'Sony Xperia Z5 And Xperia Z5 Premium Dual-SIM', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '458-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-10-25 11:05:13', '2015-10-25 05:35:13', '', 458, 'http://thetechlog.in/2